info.title: Oura API
info.description:
# Overview 

The Oura API allows Oura users and partner applications to improve their user experience with Oura data.

This document describes the Oura API Version 2 (V2), which supports access to the latest Oura Ring data types.
 For access to other data types—which have not yet migrated to V2—refer to the [Oura API Version 1 (V1)](https://cloud.ouraring.com/docs/) documentation.

# Data Access

Individual Oura users can access their own data through the API by using a [Personal Access Token](https://cloud.ouraring.com/personal-access-tokens).

If you want to retrieve data for multiple users, a registered [API Application](https://cloud.ouraring.com/oauth/applications) is required.
 API Applications are limited to **10** users before requiring approval from Oura. There is no limit once an application is approved.
 Additionally, Oura users **must provide consent** to share each data type an API Application has access to.

All data access requests through the Oura API require [Authentication](https://cloud.ouraring.com/docs/authentication).

Additionally, we recommend that Oura users keep their mobile app updated to support API access for the latest data types.
 The Oura API V2 returns a 426 response code for users who do not have an updated version of the app installed.

# Authentication

The Oura API provides two methods for Authentication: (1) the OAuth2 protocol and (2) Personal Access Tokens. For more information on the OAuth2 flow, see our [Authentication instructions](https://cloud.ouraring.com/docs/authentication).

Access tokens must be included in the request header as follows:
```http
GET /v2/usercollection/personal_info HTTP/1.1
Host: api.ouraring.com
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

# Oura HTTP Response Codes

| Response Code                        | Description |
| ------------------------------------ | - |
| 200 OK                               | Successful Response         |
| 400 Query Parameter Validation Error | The request contains query parameters that are invalid or incorrectly formatted. |
| 426 Minimum App Version Error        | The Oura user's mobile app does not meet the minimum app version requirement to support sharing the requested data type. The Oura user must update their mobile app to enable API access for the requested data type. |
| 429 Request Rate Limit Exceeded        | The API is rate limited to 5000 requests in a 5 minute period. You will receive a 429 error code if you exceed this limit. [Contact us](mailto:api-support@ouraring.com) if you expect your usage to exceed this limit.|

get.description: Returns Oura Daily Activity data for the specified Oura user within a given timeframe

schema.title: End Date
schema.description: ```YYYY-MM-DD``` formatted end date [default: current UTC date]

value.detail: Start time is greater than end time: [start_time: 2021-10-01 01:02:03+00:00; end_date: 2021-01-01 01:02:03+00:00
The user associated with this token has not updated their mobile app to support this data type.

x-codeSamples.label: cURL
x-codeSamples.source:
curl --location --request GET 'https://api.ouraring.com/v2/usercollection/daily_activity?start_date=2021-11-01&end_date=2021-12-01' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer <token>'

get.description: Returns available heart rate data for a specified Oura user within a given timeframe

schema.title: End Datetime
schema.description: ISO 8601 formatted end timestamp [default: current UTC timestamp]

value.detail: Start time is greater than end time: [start_time: 2021-10-01 01:02:03+00:00; end_date: 2021-01-01 01:02:03+00:00
The user associated with this token has not updated their mobile app to support this data type.

x-codeSamples.label: cURL
x-codeSamples.source:
# The '+' symbol in the timezone must be escaped to `%2B` if included. 
curl --location --request GET 'https://api.ouraring.com/v2/usercollection/heartrate?start_datetime=2021-11-01T00:00:00-08:00&end_datetime=2021-12-01T00:00:00-08:00' \ 
--header 'Authorization: Bearer <token>'

meet_daily_targets.title: Meet Daily Targets
meet_daily_targets.description: Contribution of meeting previous 7-day daily activity targets in range ```[1, 100]```

move_every_hour.title: Move Every Hour
move_every_hour.description: Contribution of previous 24-hour inactivity alerts in range ```[1, 100]```

recovery_time.title: Recovery Time
recovery_time.description: Contribution of previous 7-day recovery time in range ```[1, 100]```

stay_active.title: Stay Active
stay_active.description: Contribution of previous 24-hour activity in range ```[1, 100]```

training_frequency.title: Training Frequency
training_frequency.description: Contribution of previous 7-day exercise frequency in range ```[1, 100]```

training_volume.title: Training Volume
training_volume.description: Contribution of previous 7-day exercise volume in range ```[1, 100]```

class_5_min.title: Class 5 Min
class_5_min.description:
5-minute activity classification for the activity period:
* ```0```	non wear
* ```1``` rest
* ```2``` inactive
* ```3``` low activity
* ```4``` medium activity
* ```5``` high activity

equivalent_walking_distance.title: Equivalent Walking Distance
equivalent_walking_distance.description: Equivalent walking distance (in meters) of energy expenditure

high_activity_met_minutes.title: High Activity Met Minutes
high_activity_met_minutes.description: High activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in minutes

high_activity_time.title: High Activity Time
high_activity_time.description: High activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in seconds

low_activity_met_minutes.title: Low Activity Met Minutes
low_activity_met_minutes.description: Low activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in minutes

low_activity_time.title: Low Activity Time
low_activity_time.description: Low activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in seconds

medium_activity_met_minutes.title: Medium Activity Met Minutes
medium_activity_met_minutes.description: Medium activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in minutes

medium_activity_time.title: Medium Activity Time
medium_activity_time.description: Medium activity metabolic equivalent (MET) in seconds

non_wear_time.title: Non Wear Time
non_wear_time.description: The time (in seconds) in which the ring was not worn

day.title: Day
day.description: The ```YYYY-MM-DD``` formatted local date indicating when the daily activity occurred

timestamp.title: Timestamp
timestamp.description: ISO 8601 formatted local timestamp indicating the start datetime of when the daily activity occurred

activity_balance.title: Activity Balance
activity_balance.description: Contribution of cumulative activity balance in range [1, 100].

body_temperature.title: Body Temperature

hrv_balance.title: Hrv Balance

previous_night.title: Previous Night

recovery_index.title: Recovery Index
recovery_index.description: Contribution of recovery index in range [1, 100].

resting_heart_rate.title: Resting Heart Rate
resting_heart_rate.description: Contribution of resting heart rate in range [1, 100].

sleep_balance.title: Sleep Balance
sleep_balance.description: Contribution of sleep balance in range [1, 100].

timestamp.title: Timestamp
timestamp.description: ISO 8601 formatted local timestamp indicating when the heart rate data was collected

day.description: The date when the session occurred

start_datetime.title: Start Datetime

end_datetime.title: End Datetime

The user's selected mood after the session:
* ```bad```
* ```worse```
* ```same```
* ```good```

text.title: Text
text.description: Custom annotations associated with the tag, as provided by the user

timestamp.description: ISO 8601 formatted local timestamp indicating when the tag was collected

tags.title: Tags
tags.description: A list of tags selected by the user. A translation of tag values can be found [here](https://cloud.ouraring.com/edu/tag-translations).

age.title: Age
age.description: The user's age. This field is only present if the user consented to the personal access scope. Otherwise, this field will be ```null```.

weight.title: Weight
weight.description: The user's weight (in kilograms). This field is only present if the user consented to the personal access scope. Otherwise, this field will be ```null```.

height.title: Height
height.description: The user's height (in meters). This field is only present if the user consented to the personal access scope. Otherwise, this field will be ```null```.

biological_sex.title: Biological Sex
biological_sex.description: The user's biological sex. This field is only present if the user consented to the personal access scope. Otherwise, this field will be ```null```.

email.title: Email
email.description: The user's e-mail. This field is only present if the user consented to the email access scope. Otherwise, this field will be ```null```.

deep_sleep.title: Deep Sleep
deep_sleep.description: Contribution of deep sleep in range [1, 100].

efficiency.title: Efficiency
efficiency.description: Contribution of sleep efficiency in range [1, 100].

latency.title: Latency
latency.description: Contribution of sleep latency in range [1, 100].

rem_sleep.title: REM Sleep
rem_sleep.description: Contribution of REM sleep in range [1, 100].

restfulness.title: Restfulness
restfulness.description: Contribution of sleep restfulness in range [1, 100].

timing.title: Timing
timing.description: Contribution of sleep timing in range [1, 100].

total_sleep.title: Total Sleep
total_sleep.description: Contribution of total sleep in range [1, 100].

calories.title: Calories
calories.description: The number of calories (kcal) burned during the workout

day.title: Day
day.description: The ```YYYY-MM-DD``` formatted local date indicating when the workout was recorded

distance.title: Distance
distance.description: The distance (measured in meters) traveled during the workout

end_datetime.title: End Datetime
end_datetime.description: ISO 8601 formatted local timestamp indicating when the workout ended

start_datetime.title: Start Datetime
start_datetime.description: ISO 8601 formatted local timestamp indicating when the workout started

WorkoutSource.title: WorkoutSource
WorkoutSource.description:
The data source where the Workout data was collected from:
* ```manual``` Workouts which were manually entered by the user
* ```autodetected``` Workouts autodetected by Oura
* ```confirmed``` Workouts autodetected by Oura and confirmed by the user
* ```workout_heart_rate``` Workouts recorded with the Workout HR feature

bearerAuth.description: JWT Authorization header using the Bearer scheme.

tags.name: Daily Activity
tags.description: The Daily Activity scope includes daily activity summary values and detailed activity levels. Activity levels are expressed in [metabolic equivalent of task minutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolic_equivalent) (MET mins). Oura tracks activity based on the movement.

tags.name: Daily Readiness
tags.description: Readiness tells how ready you are for the day.

tags.name: Daily Sleep
tags.description: Sleep period is a nearly continuous, longish period of time spent lying down in bed.

tags.name: Heart Rate
tags.description: The Heart Rate data scope includes time-series heart rate data throughout the day and night. Heart rate is provided at 5-minute increments. For heart rate data recorded from a Session, see Sessions endpoint.

externalDocs.description: How accurate is the heart rate data generated by the Oura Ring?

tags.name: Personal Info
tags.description: The Personal Info scope includes personal information (e.g. age, email, weight, and height) about the user.

tags.name: Sessions
tags.description: The Sessions data scope provides information on how users engage with guided and unguided sessions in the Oura app, including the user’s biometric trends during the sessions.

externalDocs.description: Learn about the available session types within the Explore Tab

tags.name: Sleep Periods
tags.description: Returns Oura Sleep data for the specified Oura user within a given timeframe. A user can have multiple sleep periods per day.

tags.name: Tags
tags.description:
The Tags data scope includes tags that Oura users enter within the Oura mobile app. Tags are a growing list of activities, environment factors, symptoms, emotions, and other aspects that provide broader context into what’s happening with users beyond the objective data generated by the Oura Ring.

[More information on tag translations](https://cloud.ouraring.com/edu/tag-translations)

tags.name: Workouts
tags.description: The Workout data scope includes information about user workouts. This is a diverse, growing list of workouts that help inform how the user is training and exercising.
